\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where the unlabled arrows are the obvious ones and 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi$
\end_inset

 is defined as follows: Given 
\begin_inset Formula $p\in P$
\end_inset

, choose 
\begin_inset Formula $\widetilde{p}\in M$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $g(\widetilde{p})=p$
\end_inset

.
 Then set 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi(p)=\overline{\widetilde{p}}$
\end_inset

.
 This is well-defined since if 
\begin_inset Formula $\widetilde{p}'\in M$
\end_inset

 was another lift of 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

, then 
\begin_inset Formula $g(\widetilde{p}-\widetilde{p}')=0$
\end_inset

 implies 
\begin_inset Formula $\widetilde{p}-\widetilde{p}'\in\mbox{Ker}(g)=\mbox{Im}(f)$
\end_inset

.
 So 
\begin_inset Formula $\widetilde{p}'=f(k)+\widetilde{p}$
\end_inset

 for some 
\begin_inset Formula $k\in K$
\end_inset

, and hence 
\begin_inset Formula $\overline{\widetilde{p}'}=\overline{f(k)+\widetilde{p}}=\overline{\widetilde{p}}$
\end_inset

.
 It is also easy to verify that all vertical arrows are in fact 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

-module isomorphisms.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{example}
\backslash
label{sessplits1}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $I$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $J$
\end_inset

 be ideals in 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $I+J=R$
\end_inset

.
 Then there is a short exact sequence of 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-modules given by
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
