\end_layout

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\iota_{i}$
\end_inset

 is the inclusion map and 
\begin_inset Formula $\widetilde{\varphi}_{i}$
\end_inset

 is just 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi_{i}$
\end_inset

 but with range 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathrm{im}\,\varphi_{i}$
\end_inset

 rather than 
\begin_inset Formula $M_{i-1}$
\end_inset

.
 In fact, since 
\begin_inset Formula $\ker\varphi_{i-1}=\mathrm{im}\,\varphi_{i}$
\end_inset

, we can rewrite 
\begin_inset ERT
