\begin_layout Standard
(2
\begin_inset Formula $\implies$
\end_inset

3): Suppose that 
\begin_inset Formula $E'$
\end_inset

 is an injective 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

-module such that 
\begin_inset Formula $M\subset E'\subset E$
\end_inset

.
 Then the map 
\begin_inset Formula $E'\subset E$
\end_inset

 splits, so 
\begin_inset Formula $E=E'\oplus N$
\end_inset

 for some 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

