end{proof}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Cohen-Macaulay Modules
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{defn}
\backslash
label{defn1}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $(R,\mathfrak{m})$
\end_inset

 be a local ring and let 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

 be a finitely generated 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-module.
 We say 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

 is a 
\series bold
Cohen-Macaulay module 
\series default
if 
\begin_inset Formula $M=0$
\end_inset

 or 
\begin_inset Formula $M\neq0$
\end_inset

 and
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathrm{depth}\,M=\dim M.
\]

\end_inset

If 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathrm{depth}\,M=\dim R$
\end_inset

, then 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

 is called 
\series bold
maximal Cohen-Macaulay
\series default
.
 We say 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

 is a 
\series bold
Cohen-Macaulay ring 
\series default
if it is a Cohen-Macaulay 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-module.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{defn}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{lemma}
\backslash
label{lemma2}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 be a Noetherian ring, 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

 a finitely generated 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

-module, and 
\begin_inset Formula $I\subset A$
\end_inset

 an ideal with 
\begin_inset Formula $IM\neq M$
\end_inset

.
 Then the following are equivalent:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $\mbox{Ext}_{A}^{i}(N,M)=0$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $i<n$
\end_inset

 and all finitely generated 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

-modules 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 with 
\begin_inset Formula $\mbox{Supp}(N)\subset\mathbf{V}(I)$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $\mbox{Ext}_{A}^{i}(A/I,M)=0$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $i<n$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $\mbox{Ext}_{A}^{i}(N,M)=0$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $i<n$
\end_inset

 and some finitely generated 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

-module 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 with 
\begin_inset Formula $\mbox{Supp}(N)=\mathbf{V}(I)$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $I$
\end_inset

 contains an 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

-sequence of length 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{lemma}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{proof}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 (1) implies (2) is obvious since 
\begin_inset Formula $\mbox{Supp}(A/I)=V(I)$
\end_inset

.
 Also, (2) implies (3) is obvious since 
\begin_inset Formula $A/I$
\end_inset

 is some finitely generated 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

-module with 
\begin_inset Formula $\mbox{Supp}(A/I)=V(I)$
\end_inset

.
 To prove (3) implies (4), let 
\begin_inset Formula $n>0$
\end_inset

 and assume first that 
\begin_inset Formula $I$
\end_inset

 contains only zero divisors of 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

, that is, 
\begin_inset Formula $I$
\end_inset

 is contained in an associated prime ideal 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathfrak{p}=0:m$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 is some nonzero element in 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

.
 Then the map 
\begin_inset Formula $A/\mathfrak{p}\to M$
\end_inset

, defined by 
\begin_inset Formula $1\mapsto m$
\end_inset

, is injective.
 Localizing a 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathfrak{p}$
\end_inset

, we obtain that 
\begin_inset Formula $\mbox{Hom}_{A_{\mathfrak{p}}}(k,M_{\mathfrak{p}})\neq0$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $k=A_{\mathfrak{p}}/\mathfrak{p}A_{\mathfrak{p}}$
\end_inset

.
 Now 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathfrak{p}\in V(I)=\mbox{supp}(N)$
\end_inset

, that is, 
\begin_inset Formula $N_{\mathfrak{p}}\neq0$
\end_inset

, and hence, 
\begin_inset Formula $N_{\mathfrak{p}}/\mathfrak{p}N_{\mathfrak{p}}=N\otimes_{A}k\neq0$
\end_inset

